And I don't want any people posting and saying &quot;Atari 2600!&quot; or &quot;Genesis!&quot;</FONT><FORM method=post action="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm40.processVote?topicID=533.topic"><table border=0 cellpadding=3 cellspacing=0 width="55%"><tbody><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="1"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Sega Dreamcast</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="2"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Sony PlayStation2</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="3"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Nintendo GameCube</FONT></td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choice" value="4"><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Microsoft Xbox</FONT></td></tr></tbody></table><P><input type=submit value="Vote"><a HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm40.showMessage?topicID=533.topic&pollResults=on><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Show results</FONT></A> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eaminwhitefalcon>Eamin Whitefalcon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>¡Viva la inquisición!</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/29/02 2:12:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=533.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.tampabay.rr.com/eqsite/Eamin_small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best gaming system</span><hr size=1> I'll say PS2 because of the games. It's a very versatile system, but we don't buy gaming consoles for their ability to play CDs or DVDs. We buy them for the games.<br>
The PS2 has some of the best games for every genre out there. Fighting, RPG, racing, action, sports, you name it, PS2 has it. Some of the genres have only one or two great new games out at the moment, but we have the huge PS1 library of titles to keep us semi-occupied until more games are churned out.<br>
<br>
I put Dreamcast on the list because I didn't want a three-console poll.<br>
<br>
GameCube has some very well-established serieses (like Zelda), but it fails miserably in some genres. For example, the fighting category is horribly underdeveloped.<br>
<br>
The Xbox has some great titles (like Halo), but there isn't enough variety, IMO. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eaminwhitefalcon>Eamin Whitefalcon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>¡Viva la inquisición!</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/29/02 2:43:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=533.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.tampabay.rr.com/eqsite/Eamin_small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best gaming system</span><hr size=1> WTH are people voting for Dreamcast? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utaerendur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taerendur</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.liquid2k.com/lanzajr/DGBoardsig2.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/29/02 2:43:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=533.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best gaming system</span><hr size=1> Well, are you asking what system is in itself the best, or just what has the best games?  If it's the first question, then X-Box beats them all hands down.  I has the best hardware of the group and can do more than any of them out of the box.  You have to upgrade a PS2 and GC to get online capabilities and storage of an X-Box.<br>
<br>
If it's games, then of course the PS2 has them all beat.  Everyone and their mother is making games for PS2, no matter how hard it is to develop for.  However, even though it has a huge library, I'm really not impressed with the games out for PS2.  I'd say there are only about 10 standout titles that would make me buy this system, the rest is crap.  GT3 made me pick up my system, and since then only FFX has made me feel good about that purchase.  So far, I love playing my X-Box and Dreamcast far more than PS2. <p><html>
